                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d913">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.515/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Appointed Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-29T10:00:00+03:06"
                            >May 29, 1943—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:48 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>46. Cairo’s 928, May 21, 6 p.m. On receipt of a reply to Cairo’s 861, May 11,
                    further consideration can be given to acute Saudi currency problem.</p>
                <p>British Legation here has just requested an additional 100,000 sovereigns for
                    current needs of local government.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Cairo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
